<h3 class='scout-h3'>Appendix</h3>
  <p>
    <ol type="I">
      <li><strong>Impedance</strong><br>Impedance is the amount of resistance that a component offers to current flow in a circuit at 
        a specific frequency.</li>
      <li><strong>Standing Wave Ratio</strong><br>SWR is so imporant as the value connects the voltage and 
      power, respectively that is reflected by the end terminal here the antenna. The higher the SWR the more
      energy of the original signal is lost. <br>For example, a ratio of 1.5:1 already reflects 20% of the voltage with a power 
      reflection of 4%. That is already a high loss for your signal. 
      </li>
    </ol>
    
  </p>


